HEADWORD: Milquetoast
<hw>Milquetoast</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Caspar Milquetoast, a
character in a cartoon strip by H. T. Webster, <publ>The Timid
Soul</publ> (1935).]</ety> <def>a timid, unassertive man or boy fearful
of confrontation and easily manipulated and dominated.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> sissy, pantywaist, pansy, milksop.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

